1. The program requires three command line arguments a) Source Path - Enron EBS Mount Directory b) Interim Path - To hold unzipped files temporarily. c) Destination Path - For storing output Jsons

2. The output is stored in json files

3. Databricks xml parser is used extensively as it is easier to work with Dataframes. The corresponding jar is placed in lib folder

4. It is advised to create fat jar using "sudo sbt assembly" command and then submit it in an appropriate server

5. As the data is fairly big with reasonable processing requirement, it is advised to submit the jar in a minimum 4 Node cluster
